At this point, it is important to emphasise that the explained model assumes the following simplifications: severe cases are treated at hospital while patients developing smooth symptoms stay at home; no previous co-morbidity nor sex distinction is taken into account; ICU patients come from previous hospital stages only and finally, each age band has a fixed initial population, i.e. births, mortality by other causes and moving between age bands are not considered. This last assumption is fairly true for short/medium term simulations. Following the previous description and taking into account the nomenclature of Fig.¬†1, the dynamic expressions corresponding to the states of each age band (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
