Risk contacts matrix (5-year width bands)

The model presented in the previous section was adjusted to represent the pandemic evolution in Argentina by using the National Health Ministry database adequately processed [21]. Although this public register presents many data fields, it does not allow to determine all the model parameters. To overcome this gap some of them were then taken from the specialised literature. Table¬†3 shows the parameters obtained from the literature [22‚Äì24]. Tables¬†4 and¬†5 show the parameters obtained from National Health Ministry databases. In Table¬†4, œÉs, Œº and œÅ are shared by more than one age band due to their similarities.
